
PyXMPP -- Python Jabber/XMPPP implementation
________________________________________________________________________________


Introduction
¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯
Jabber Feed Notifier [JFN] is a Jabber client/component that send notifications 
of new feeds entries. You can configure it to send you only notifications, 
summary message or full message, and more. In addition, you can send your OPML 
file.


Requirements
¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯
JFN will need:
    - Python <http://www.python.org>, version >=2.4
    - xmpppy <http://xmpppy.sourceforge.net>, version >=3.0
    - feedparser <http://feedparser.org>, version =4.1
        - (recommended) iconv_codec and cjkcodecs <http://cjkpython.i18n.org>, 
        for feedparser's charset detection
    - Durus <http://www.mems-exchange.org/software/durus/>, version =3.3. 
    JFN use this as database (no SQL), it's a Persistence System.


Download
¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯
Get the latest stable versions 
<http://developer.berlios.de/project/filelist.php?group_id=6632> from BerliOS 
files system or development version with experimental features 
<http://developer.berlios.de/svn/?group_id=6632> fom BerliOS SVN.


Installation
¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯
Edit configuration file config-example.cfg and rename it to config.cfg (by 
default).

Give right permisions for "data" directory to allow write it.

Execute JFN using:
    python jfn.py &
or:
    ./jfn.py &


